            <thetext>Try to order the Artist column in the table of the Showcase and look at the end of the table. 
The last 5 rows are in wrong order. 
I think that this is a bug in the ordering function and maybe it can depend by some problems in managing empty cells because if you fill the empty cell the ordering works well.



I  think also that a &quot;caseInsensitive&quot; property should be added to the table class. 
Now uppercase letters come before lowercase letters, but i think that this is not always the right behaviour for the user.

For example: &quot;Dog&quot;,&quot;mouse&quot;,&quot;cat&quot;

Without caseInsensitive property(current behaviour) become: 
&quot;Dog&quot;,&quot;cat&quot;,&quot;mouse&quot;

With caseInsensitive property should be: 
&quot;cat&quot;,&quot;Dog&quot;,&quot;mouse&quot;</thetext>
          </long_desc>
